== Ingrid Patch ==
* Ingrid released
<br>

== '''Universal Changes''' ==
* '''{{clr|DR|Wakeup Drive Reversal}}'''
** When the invincible startup interacts with an opponent's Throw hitbox, a 12f screen freeze now occurs and refunds {{clr|DR|1 Drive bar}} on hit
** This does not prevent Burnout from occurring before the meter is gained, but it makes {{clr|DR|Drive Reversal}} a more cost-effective defensive tool against throw loops
** As an unintended consequence, the screen freeze affects Kimberly's spraycan setups, causing the opponent's {{clr|DR|Wakeup Drive Reversal}} to be punishable if she attempts a throw
* '''{{clr|PC|Punish Counter}} Throws'''
** The opponent no longer gains double the usual amount of {{clr|SA|Super Gauge}} (no change to attacker's meter gain)
** This makes {{clr|PC|Punish Counter}} Throws a more desirable option to finish a round while building meter without also benefiting the opponent
* '''Throw Escapes'''
** Defender's Drive Gain reduced 10000 → 5000
** Defender's Super Gain reduced 1000 → 0
* '''{{clr|SA|Super}} Projectile Clashes'''
** Changed the behavior of clashing multi-hit projectile {{clr|SA|Supers}} to ensure consistent results
* '''{{clr|SA|Super Art}} Command Inputs'''
** Fixed issue where holding a specific direction would cause some {{clr|SA|Supers}} not to be performed
** Affected {{clr|SA|Supers}}: 
*** Akuma {{clr|SA|SA2}} (Modern + Manual, while holding Up)
*** C. Viper {{clr|SA|SA1}} (Modern + Manual, while holding Down or Back)
*** Chun-Li {{clr|SA|SA1/SA2/SA3}} (Modern + Manual, while holding Up)
*** Ed {{clr|SA|SA3}} (Classic, while holding Back)
*** Mai {{clr|SA|SA1/SA2/SA3}} (Modern + Manual, while holding Up)
*** Ryu {{clr|SA|SA2}} (Modern + Manual, while holding Up or Down)
<br>

== '''Character Changes''' ==

=== '''Alex''' ===
* {{clr|M|Assist Combo 2}}
** Fixed issue where input buffer would be disabled after the 2nd hit was blocked when attempting to use another {{clr|M|Assist Combo 2}}
** Input buffer for the 2nd hit shifted from frame 2 → 7
* {{clr|H|Twisted Drop}} (Modern Controls: {{clr|L|2L}}~{{clr|H|2H}})
** Fixed issue where 2nd attack would not be performed while holding the Assist button
* {{clr|M|Palm Strikes}} (Modern Controls: {{clr|M|5M}}~{{clr|M|M}})
** Fixed issue where 2nd attack would not be performed while holding the Assist button
* Dangerous Armbar (Modern Controls: 2{{clr|M|M}}{{clr|H|H}}~2{{clr|L|L}}{{clr|M|M}})
** Fixed issue where immediate scaling was unintentionally applied when using the Throw button instead of {{clr|L|L}}{{clr|M|M}}
* Hyper Takedown (2PP~2{{clr|L|LPLK}})
** 20% Immediate scaling added to match other normal throws
<br>

=== '''C. Viper''' ===
* {{clr|H|Assist Combo 3}}
** Fixed issue where the input buffer for the 2nd attack was faster than expected during the 1st hit
<br>

=== '''Chun-Li''' ===
* {{clr|M|Snake Strike}} (Modern Controls: 214X~{{clr|M|5M}})
** Fixed issue where the {{clr|PC|Punish Counter}} state was extended by 1 frame when holding Up after being Perfect Parries
<br>

=== '''Dhalsim''' ===
* Aerial Yoga Teleport Forward (j.6PPP)
** Fixed issue where Dhalsim could appear behind the opponent facing the wrong direction if both players were cornered
<br>

=== '''Ed''' ===
